{% extends "default.jinja" %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="theme-area">
        <div class="content">
            <div class="container">
                <h1>Call for Communities</h1>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container document">
        <div class="content row">
            <div class="col s12 m8 l10">
                <p>
                    Hong Kong Open Source Conference (HKOSCon) is aimed to promote,
                    support and develop open source projects and communities.
                    To address our mission, we revises our process and styles every year,
                    and makes any changes if necessary.
                </p>
                <p>
                    HKOSCon 2018 is now calling for open source communities to participate and host their sessions and activities.
                    We looks forward to cooperate with your community to support and contribute the open source community.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Your community can host your own sessions in your track,
                    a community track can promote open source projects developed by your community.
                </p>

                <div id="import-date" class="scrollspy">
                    <h3>Import Date</h3>
                    <p>
                        <strong>Community Registration:</strong>
                        <a href="https://goo.gl/forms/75Sxnd8lmKSGbweE3" target="_blank">https://goo.gl/forms/75Sxnd8lmKSGbweE3</a>
                        <br>
                        <strong>Closing date of this call:</strong> 30 November 2017.<br>
                        <strong>Tentative CFP Month:</strong> January 2018.<br>
                        <strong>Tentative Conference Month:</strong> June 2018.<br>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div id="entitled" class="scrollspy">
                    <h3>Your community will be entitled with:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>2 30-min sessions or more.</li>
                        <li>Program vetting for CFP of your track.</li>
                        <li>Inviting your speaker(s) for your track.</li>
                        <li>Logo is listed as "participating communities" in alphabetical order on conference website.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="responsibility" class="scrollspy">
                    <h3>Responsibility of your community</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Calls for proposals (CFP) in January in your community.
                            At least 50% of your sessions are from CFP of your track.
                            Sharing all CFP data with the conference program team.
                        </li>
                        <li>Promote sessions of your track and the conference in your community in March to June.</li>
                        <li>Host and manage all sessions in your track.</li>
                        <li>Taking photos for your sessions and activities, uploading to your community.</li>
                        <li>Assist video recording for your track.</li>
                        <li>
                            Submit a summary report (200+ words) with attendance data of your sessions and activities,
                            uploaded photos, your comments and suggestions.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div id="requirements" class="scrollspy">
                    <h3>Requirements</h3>
                    <p>Open source community applying this scheme must released source codes in one of open source licenses.</p>
                </div>

                <div id="discussion" class="scrollspy">
                    <h3>Discussion and Q&A</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/opensourcehk/permalink/1593669263987325/" target="_blank">
                                Facebook Group
                            </a>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <a href="https://hackmd.io/s/r1iDRMBiW" target="_blank">HackMD</a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col hide-on-small-only m3 l2">
                <div class="toc-wrapper scrollspy">
                    <div>
                        <ul class="section table-of-contents">
                            <li><a href="#import-date">Import Date</a></li>
                            <li><a href="#entitled">Your community will be entitled with</a></li>
                            <li><a href="#responsibility">Responsibility of your community</a></li>
                            <li><a href="#requirements">Requirements</a></li>
                            <li><a href="#discussion">Discussion and Q&A</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}